  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale input data)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A turbulence-closure update was applied to the CFD solver on 2025-11-10, constituting the current modelRevisionDate. The primary experimental dataset used to anchor model inputs carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-18 — approximately three weeks before the revision. The assessment team judged the turbulence-closure change 'not material' to the dataset's applicability because the affected sub-model governs near-wall eddy viscosity in regions argued to be remote from the hemolysis-dominant blade-tip zones. No formal re-validation against post-revision predictions was performed; the dataset was carried forward without re-qualification.",
