      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Biological variability of blood samples characterised; minimum n=6 independent donors per operating point; lot-to-lot variation documented.",
      "rationale": "Experiments used pooled bovine blood from a single lot. Human donor variability was not characterised. Sample size per operating point was n=3, below the required n=6. Biological variability is an uncharacterised epistemic gap. Achieved level 2 vs. required level 3."
