    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that input parameters used in validation experiments are equivalent to those applicable in clinical COU; species and fluid equivalency argued with supporting data.",
      "rationale": "Bovine blood was used in validation experiments; clinical COU involves human blood. Viscosity and density corrections were applied using published conversion factors. Viscoelastic differences between bovine and human erythrocytes under high-shear conditions were not characterised. Equivalency of input parameters is partially supported but not formally demonstrated. Achieved level 2 vs. required level 3."
    }
